Expand and simplify completely: \begin{align*}
x\left(x(1+x)+2x\right)-3(x^2-x+2)
\end{align*}

For integers $n$, let \[f(n) = \left\{
\begin{array}{cl}
n^2 + 1 & \text{ if }n\text{ is odd}, \\
n^2 - 3n + 1 & \text{ if }n\text{ is even}.
\end{array}
\right.\]Find $f(f(f(f(f(f(2))))))$.

Suppose that $a$ and $b$ are positive real numbers, and let \[f(x) =
\begin{cases}
\frac{a}{b}x & \text{ if }x\le-4, \\
abx^2 & \text{ if }x>-4.
\end{cases}
\]If $f(-4)=-\frac{60}{13}$ and $f(4)=3120$, what is $a+b$?

For what negative value of $k$ is there exactly one solution to the system of equations \begin{align*}
y &= 2x^2 + kx + 6 \\
y &= -x + 4?
\end{align*}

Find $a+b+c$, given that $x+y\neq -1$ and  \begin{align*}
ax+by+c&=x+7,\\
a+bx+cy&=2x+6y,\\
ay+b+cx&=4x+y.
\end{align*}

